# Presentation Software Agent Notes
# Stack: Node workspace
# Updated: 2026-05-04 (onboarded to Kunida Rules Network — RCA-208)

## Network Inheritance

This repo inherits rules from the Kunida Rules Network. Read order (highest precedence to lowest):

1. **This file** (`.cursorrules`) — site-specific business facts, locks, brand tokens.
2. **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** — local hard rules and overrides.
3. **`.cursor/rules/local-*.mdc`** + **`.cursor/rules/local-borrowed/`** — local experiments and patterns adopted from `Kunida-Patterns-Library`.
4. **`.cursor/rules/inherited/stack/`** — stack-specific rules from `Kunida-WordPress-Rules-Core` (this Node workspace falls back to the WP core; PHP rules don't apply, but workspace/docs/source-control rules are useful) (read-only).
5. **`.cursor/rules/inherited/shared/`** — stack-agnostic rules from `Kunida-Shared-Business-Rules` (read-only).

Local always wins. Run `npm run sync:rules` to refresh inherited rules. Inheritance contract: `Kunida-Rules-Network/docs/RULES-SOURCES.md`.

To browse adoptable patterns from other Kunida sites: `npm run patterns:browse`. To verify isolation: `npm run check:local-isolation`. To audit duplication: `npm run check:rule-duplication`.

