## Where to look

- Project orient + workflows: `AGENTS.md` (if present), `README.md`, `docs/AGENT-CONTEXT.md` (if present).
- Single sources of truth: `docs/ops/SINGLE-SOURCES-OF-TRUTH.md` (if present).
- Network rules: `.cursor/rules/inherited/` (read-only, refreshed via `npm run sync:rules`).

## Source-control discipline

Inherited from `Kunida-Shared-Business-Rules` HR-028: `git add -A` → commit → push every agent run. Do not regress this rule.

## Promotion path

If you find yourself writing a rule here that applies to >1 Kunida site, consider:
1. Drafting it in this file as `HR-LOCAL-NNN` (site-specific).
2. After validation, promoting it to `Kunida-Shared-Business-Rules` (cross-stack) or the appropriate stack core.
3. Document the promotion in `docs/ops/DECISION-LOG.md` with an RCA reference.
